  "overnight": false,
  "slug": "spicy-quick-pickled-cucumbers",
  "source": "This recipe is based on Roy Choi’s recipe from MasterClass.",
  "steps": [
    {
      "name": "",
      "steps": [
        {
          "text": "In a frying pan set over medium heat, toast star anise for a few minutes, until it releases its fragrance.",
          "pause": false
        },
        {
          "text": "While the start anis is toasting, trim the cucumbers, and slice them into 1/2 cm disks.",
          "pause": false
        },
        {
          "text": "Add a bit of sesame oil to the pan. Once it starts to shimmer, add the cucumbers.",
          "pause": false
        },
        {
          "text": "Add the <Ingredient name=\"sesame seeds\"  />, <Ingredient name=\"chile flakes\"  />, <Ingredient name=\"coconut sugar\"  />, <Ingredient name=\"peppercorn\" modifier=\"black\" />, <Ingredient name=\"cumin seeds\"  />, <Ingredient name=\"salt\"  />, lime juice, <Ingredient name=\"vinegar\"  />, and <Ingredient name=\"water\"  />; and stir thoroughly.",
          "pause": false
        },
        {
          "text": "Bring to boil, and cook for 1-2 minutes more, until the cucumbers just start to soften and absorb the sauce.",
          "pause": false
        },
        {
          "text": "Transfer the cucumbers with the sauce into a sealable container, and refrigerate for at least 30 minutes before serving.",
          "pause": false
        }
      ]
    }
  ],
